Step-by-Step Guide to Enable Gmail API in Google Developer Console
1Ô∏è‚É£ Go to Google Cloud Console
Open Google Cloud Console.

Sign in with your Google account.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Create a New Project
Click on the project selector at the top.

Click "New Project".

Enter a Project Name (e.g., Gmail API Project).

Click Create.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Enable the Gmail API
Go to the Gmail API page.

Click "Enable" to activate the API for your project.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Create OAuth Credentials
In the left menu, go to "APIs & Services" ‚Üí "Credentials".

Click "Create Credentials" ‚Üí "OAuth Client ID".

If asked to configure consent screen, do this first:

Choose "External" (for personal use).

Set up the basic app name, email, and scope.

Click Save and Continue.

Back in the OAuth creation:

Select Application type: "Desktop app".

Click Create.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Download Credentials
After creating the OAuth client, click "Download JSON".

Rename the file to credentials.json.

Store it in the same directory as your Python script.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Configure OAuth Consent Screen
Before creating credentials, you must set up the OAuth consent screen:

In the left menu, go to "APIs & Services" ‚Üí "OAuth consent screen".

Choose "External" (if using for personal Gmail).

Click Create and fill in:

App Name (e.g., "Gmail API App").

User Support Email (your Gmail).

Developer Contact Email (your Gmail).

Click Save and Continue.

In the Scopes section, click Add or Remove Scopes ‚Üí Search for gmail ‚Üí Select:


4Ô∏è‚É£ Create OAuth Credentials
Go to "APIs & Services" ‚Üí "Credentials".

Click "Create Credentials" ‚Üí "OAuth Client ID".

Select Application Type: "Desktop app".

Click Create ‚Üí Download JSON.

Rename the file to credentials.json and save it in your project folder.



